# - Use survey-weighted logistic regression across multiply imputed datasets
# - Pool coefficients and covariance matrices using Rubin's rules
# - Estimate:
#     (1) overall association for each exposure
#     (2) non-linearity for each exposure
#     (3) linear-by-linear interaction
# - Visualize:
#     (A) marginal curve for circadian misalignment score
#     (B) marginal curve for weekday sleep duration
#     (C) 2D joint effect heatmap
#
# NOTES:
# - Observational and cross-sectional only; no causal language.
# - P-values are derived from MI-pooled Wald tests.
# - Default outcome: PHQ-8 >= 10
################################################################################

